item.dc:creator: @tobias222 tobias222
item.description:
@tobias222 wrote:

[quote=“TeleNubby, post:5, topic:217965”][quote author=tobias222 link=topic=286450.msg2319512#msg2319512 date=1215449909]
replace everything in your run.bat with:

java -cp . client

Try that.
[/quote]Why the hell would you add the -classpath parameter if you aren’t going to use it?[/quote]

I had a problem like that once, so I asked Mod Taharok and he told me to do that and it worked.
Doesn’t always work though, so I said “try” that.

Don't listen to Tobias. As that will screw it up.

How would that “screw it up” ? If things got ugly you could probably press “ctrl+z” and save. (ctrl+z = undo)
But I am sure its something you have to edit in the run batch file.
